      "short_description": "Creates and configures a Secrets Manager private certificates engine",
      "long_description": "This deployable architecture sets up a private certificates engine within IBM Cloud Secrets Manager. A private certificates engine is used to issue and manage private TLS certificates that are trusted only within your organization, rather than by public Certificate Authorities. The module provisions a Root Certificate Authority, an Intermediate Certificate Authority, and a Certificate Template to define policies for certificate issuance. \n\nℹ️ This Terraform-based automation is part of a broader suite of IBM-maintained Infrastructure as Code (IaC) assets, each following the naming pattern \"Cloud automation for *servicename*\" and focusing on single IBM Cloud service. These single-service deployable architectures can be used on their own to streamline and automate service deployments through an [IaC approach](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/secure-enterprise?topic=secure-enterprise-understanding-projects), or assembled together into a broader [automated IaC stack](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/secure-enterprise?topic=secure-enterprise-config-stack) to automate the deployment of an end-to-end solution architecture.",
      "offering_docs_url": "https://github.com/terraform-ibm-modules/terraform-ibm-secrets-manager-private-cert-engine/blob/main/README.md",
      "offering_icon_url": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/terraform-ibm-modules/terraform-ibm-secrets-manager-private-cert-engine/main/images/secrets_manager_private_cert_engine.svg",
      "provider_name": "IBM",
      "features": [
        {
          "title": "Root Certificate Authority",
          "description": "Creates an internally signed root certificate authority (CA) for your service instance. It acts as the trust anchor for a certificates chain and can be used to sign a lower level or subordinate CA. [Learn more](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/secrets-manager?topic=secrets-manager-root-certificate-authorities&interface=ui)."
        },
        {
          "title": "Intermediate Certificate Authority",
          "description": "Creates and configures an [intermediate certificate authority](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/secrets-manager?topic=secrets-manager-intermediate-certificate-authorities&interface=ui) to sign and issue certificates to an end-entity, such as an app or website."
        },
        {
          "title": "Certificate template",
          "description": "Creates and manages [certificate templates](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/secrets-manager?topic=secrets-manager-certificate-templates&interface=ui) to define the parameters to apply to the private certificates."
        }
      ],
      "support_details": "This product is in the community registry, as such support is handled through the [original repo](https://github.com/terraform-ibm-modules/terraform-ibm-secrets-manager-private-cert-engine). If you experience issues please open an issue [here](https://github.com/terraform-ibm-modules/terraform-ibm-secrets-manager-private-cert-engine/issues). Please note this product is not supported via the IBM Cloud Support Center.",
